reviews.text:
When arriving home from Southport and having two single prams and myself not being that good. Their was no lift down no sign to say what to do if disabled and having prams etc so very p##### off had to carry prams down then up stairs my husband who has a very bad knee had to carry prams with baby's in ruined the end of our day.

Mrs k Whitehead

Left my bag there this morning due to commuting problems getting to the station. I was contacting work to let them know I was running late when my train arrived. I was able to call through and get them to hold my bag for me and when I returned, they recognised me and returned the bag, so obviously very pleased.
Great for trainspotting with the trains doing 90-100 here
Can't fault it, superb location and great views. Could easily spend 2-3 hours here
Cause my partner lives near bye and station easy to get to
